es.com/news/tv/2019-08-21/peter-capaldi-to-star-in-new-bbc4-christmas-ghost-story/|title=Peter Capaldi to star in new BBC4 Christmas ghost story|author=Fullerton, Huw|date=21 August 2019|website=[[Radio Times]]|accessdate=21 August 2019}}</ref> || \n|}\n\n===Stage===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 1974\n| ''[[An Inspector Calls]]''\n|\n| Fort Theatre\n|-\n| 1976\n| ''Whaur's yer Willie Wallace noo?''\n|\n| Strathclyde Theatre Group\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 1983\n| ''John, Paul, George, Ringo and Bert''\n| [[John Lennon]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"| [[Young Vic]]\n|-\n| ''[[Twelfth Night]]''\n| Fabian\n|-\n| ''[[The Duenna]]''\n|\n|-\n| ''Doom Doom Doom''\n|\n| [[Royal Court Theatre]]\n|-\n| ''[[Othello]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1984\n| ''[[Blood Brothers (musical)|Blood Brothers]]''\n| Eddie\n| UK tour\n|-\n| ''[[Dracula]]''\n| [[Jonathan Harker]]\n| [[Half Moon Theatre]]\n|-\n| 1985\n| ''Songs for Stray Cats and Other Living Creatures''\n| Graeme\n| [[Paines Plough|Paines Plough Theatre]]\n|-\n| 1986\n| ''All the Fun of the Fair''\n|\n| [[Half Moon Theatre]]\n|-\n| 1987\n| ''Cabaret Downstairs''\n| Mr. Meekie\n| [[Traverse Theatre]]\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''The Tom and Sammy Jo Show''\n| Tom\n| [[Tron Theatre]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1989\n| ''Valued Friends''\n| Howard\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[Hampstead Theatre]]\n|-\n| ''Treats''\n| Patrick\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Murder Is Easy]]''\n| Luke Fitzwilliam\n| [[Duke of York's Theatre]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"| 1998\n|rowspan=\"3\"| ''[[The Judas Kiss (play)|The Judas Kiss]]''\n|rowspan=\"3\"| [[Robbie Ross]]\n| [[Almeida Theatre]]\n|-\n| [[Playhouse Theatre]]\n|-\n| [[Broadhurst Theatre]]\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''Feelgood''\n| Paul\n| [[Garrick Theatre]]\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''Absurdia''\n| Various characters\n| [[Donmar Warehouse]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2011\u201312\n|rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[The Ladykillers (play)|The Ladykillers]]''\n|rowspan=\"2\"| Professor Marcus\n| [[Liverpool Playhouse]]\n|-\n| [[Gielgud Theatre